## inv-angular Migration Guardrails

These rules are mandatory for all future work and all React -> Angular migrations in this repository.
If a generated solution conflicts with these rules, regenerate until compliant.

### 1) UI & Design System (Mandatory)

- Use **NG-ZORRO** components for all UI controls and layouts whenever an equivalent exists.
- Use project design tokens and brand palette only (Tailwind tokens like `brand-primary`, `brand-dark`, `brand-success`, `brand-warning`, `brand-error`, surface tokens).
- Enforce consistent control sizing:
  - Global border radius: `6px`
  - Standard form control height: `38px`
  - Applies to input/select/number/date/textarea wrappers (according to existing global styles).
- Table action pattern:
  - If a row has more than one action, use `nz-dropdown` for row actions.
  - Do not place multiple inline action buttons directly in table rows when dropdown is expected.
- Active/inactive state pattern:
  - Always use the shared `StatusToggleComponent` for status toggling in tables/forms where applicable.
- Empty state pattern:
  - Always use the shared `EmptyStateComponent` (`app-empty-state`) when a list/table has no data.
  - Pass `title` and optionally `message` as inputs (use translation keys via `| translate`).
  - For `nz-table`, use `[nzNoResult]` with an `ng-template` that contains `<app-empty-state>`.
  - Do not introduce custom empty-state markup or the default Ng-Zorro "No Data" placeholder.
- Icons:
  - Use **Lucide Angular** only.
  - Default icon stroke width must be `2`.

### 2) Technical Architecture (Mandatory)

- Use **Angular 21 Standalone Components** only.
- Use **Signals** for local and shared state management (`signal`, `computed`, `effect` patterns as needed).
- Use Angular's new template control flow syntax only:
  - `@if`, `@for`, `@switch`
  - Avoid legacy structural syntax (`*ngIf`, `*ngFor`) in new/updated migrated code unless required for third-party APIs.
- All HTTP/data-access calls must go through services that extend or use the project's `BaseApiService`.
- Confirmation safety:
  - **NEVER** perform delete or status-toggle actions without routing through `ConfirmationService`.
  - This applies to both UI-triggered actions and programmatic flows.

### 3) Migration Source of Truth (Read-Only Context)

- During migration, treat `frontend/src/` (React codebase) as **read-only reference for business logic**.
- Re-implement logic as clean Angular 21 code that matches this project's architecture and conventions.
- Do not copy React patterns verbatim (hooks/components/state shape) when Angular-native alternatives are required.
- **Node API + Prisma for this product:** implement and migrate backend changes in `our-hotel/inv-lastest/` (not other repo `backend/` trees unless explicitly requested).
- Align all DTOs, enums, and contracts with `our-hotel/inv-lastest/prisma/schema.prisma`.
- If React behavior conflicts with Prisma schema types, Prisma schema is authoritative.

### 4) Global Status Styling (Mandatory)

- Use shared status SCSS utility classes for all status badges/chips (e.g., `.status-active`, related shared variants).
- Do not introduce ad-hoc badge color classes when a shared status class exists.
- Keep status visuals consistent across features (items, stock, ledger, movements, etc.).

### 5) Bilingual Translation (Mandatory)

- Every user-facing text must support **both English and Arabic**.
- No new hardcoded UI text in templates/components/services.
- All visible labels, placeholders, button text, alerts, toasts, confirmations, and empty states must come from translation keys.
- Use `ngx-translate` translation files (`en` + `ar`) and keep keys synchronized.
- Any new feature must ship with complete `en/ar` translations in the same PR/task.

### 6) Compliance Checklist (Before Finalizing Any Migration)

- NG-ZORRO used for UI building blocks.
- Form controls respect `6px` radius and `38px` height standards.
- Lucide icons used with stroke width `2`.
- Signals + Angular 21 standalone + `@if/@for` syntax applied.
- API calls implemented via `BaseApiService`-based services.
- Delete/toggle flows protected by `ConfirmationService`.
- Logic referenced from `frontend/src/`, types aligned with Prisma schema.
- Status badges use shared global status classes.
- Empty states use `EmptyStateComponent` with translated title/message.
- All user-facing text translated in both `en` and `ar`.

### 7) Keeping Conventions Updated

- When introducing any new shared component, pattern, or convention, add it to this `.cursorrules` file.
- This ensures consistency across migrated pages and new features.
